%I A122465 #19 Mar 31 2026 00:04:58
%S A122465 5,1521,3678726,22377473783
%N A122465 a(n) is the smallest number k such that gpf(k-j) <= floor((k-j)^(1/n)) for 0<=j<=3 where gpf(k) is the greatest prime factor of k.
%C A122465 These were found by _Robert Gerbicz_.
%C A122465 These numbers could be called "smooth power quartets".
%H A122465 Fred Schneider and R. Gerbicz, <a href="http://www.mersenneforum.org/showthread.php?t=5647">Smooth Power Trios</a>.
%e A122465 For n=2: 1521 = 3^2*13^2, 13 <= floor(sqrt(1521)) = 39; 1520 = 2^4*5*19 <= 38; 1519 = 7^2*31, 31 <= 38; 1518 = 2*3*11*23, 23 <= 38; and no number smaller than 1521 has this property.
%Y A122465 Cf. A122463, A122464.
%K A122465 hard,more,nonn
%O A122465 1,1
%A A122465 _Fred Schneider_, Sep 09 2006
%E A122465 a(2) corrected and entry edited by _Sean A. Irvine_, Mar 28 2026
